# This repository (code-guardian) is checked out at the agent's HOME root
# (/home/agent), which also contains secrets and runtime state (.ssh, .claude,
# .config, work/, ...). To make `git add -A` safe and never capture those,
# ignore EVERYTHING at the top level by default, then re-include only the
# agent-definition files this repo actually tracks.
#
# NOTE: this repo still TRACKS work/MEMORY.md and work/REVIEWS.md as seeds (so the
# in-repo links stay valid). .gitignore does not untrack files already in the index,
# so those seeds remain versioned here; the `/*` rule only hides *untracked* paths
# (HOME secrets, work/reviews/, an inner work/.git, ...). On the agent volume,
# onboarding additionally runs `git update-index --skip-worktree` on the two seed
# files so their local runtime changes are ignored.

/*

!/.gitignore
!/CLAUDE.md
!/README.md
!/ONBOARDING.md

# Never track these even if a future allowlist entry would pull them in.
.DS_Store
.claude/settings.local.json
